ion’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Ashendon was born in 1410, in Longworth, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, William Ashenden 1st, was 11407 and his mother, Mrs. Elizabeth Ashendon, was 15. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Mrs. William Ashendon. He died in 1450, in Berkshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 40."},"et":{"1410–1450":"1410–1450","1410–Female":"1410–Surnud","1410–1461":"1410–1461","1430–1518":"1430–1518","1435–1501":"1435–1501","1445–1500":"1445–1500","1393–1404":"1393–1404","1396–Female":"1396–Surnud","1 July 1435":"1. juuli 1435","About 1445":"umbes 1445","1396":"1396","1450":"1450","1461":"1461","1393":"1393","1404":"1404","1501":"1501","1435":"1435","1500":"1500","1445":"1445","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1518":"1518","Berkshire, England":"Berkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Longworth, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Longworth, Berkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Berkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Berkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Longworth, Berkshire, England":"Longworth, Berkshire, England"},"fi":{"1410–1450":"1410–1450","1410–Female":"1410–Kuollut","1410–1461":"1410–1461","1430–1518":"1430–1518","1435–1501":"1435–1501","1445–1500":"1445–1500","1393–1404":"1393–1404","1396–Female":"1396–Kuollut","1 July 1435":"1. heinäkuuta 1435","About 1445":"noin 1445","1396":"1396","1450":"1450","1461":"1461","1393":"1393","1404":"1404","1501":"1501","1435":"1435","1500":"1500","1445":"1445","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1518":"1518","Berkshire, England":"Berkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Lo